<HEADLINE> Baht Plunges to New Record Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The baht plunged further today,
setting a new record low of more than 42 baht against the US
dollar.
</P>
<P>
The selling rate today closed at 42.50-42.65 baht against one
dollar on the onshore market and it was once quoted at 43.05 baht
against one dollar.
</P>
<P>
On the offshore market, the baht also closed at 43.30-42.85
against the dollar today.
</P>
<P>
Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai today told reporters that the
slump of the baht today was mainly triggered by the turmoil on the
international monetary market.
</P>
<P>
However, local analysts said that heavy selling of the baht for
dollars by local businessmen to repay the dollar debts by the end
of this year attributed to the plunge of the baht today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
