<HEADLINE> UN Envoy for Somalia Visits Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni Vice President Abdo Rabo
Mansour Hadi today met with David Steven, visiting U.N. special
envoy for Somali affairs, the Yemeni News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Hadi discussed with Steven the Somali problem and ways of
seeking an appropriate solution, according to the agency.
</P>
<P>
He reviewed Yemen's approaches to help relieve Somalia of its
ordeal, and the impact of the Somali problem on neighboring
countries, particularly Yemen which accommodates a large number of
Somali refugees.
</P>
<P>
Steven said that the U.N. is looking forward to resolving the
Somali problem once and for all, and underscored the importance of
coordination with Yemen to seek a peaceful solution to the issue.
</P>
<P>
Hadi expressed Yemen's readiness to maintain its efforts, in
coordination with other concerned parties, to help restore peace
and stability in Somalia.
</P>
<P>
He called on the U.N. to intensify international efforts to
avert further sufferings of the Somali people, and to work out a
settlement of the crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
