<HEADLINE> Lufthansa to Test Mobile Phone Detector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The German airline Lufthansa
announced today that it will use a special electronic detector to
help trace down illegal on-board use of mobile phones.
</P>
<P>
The new device is said to be able to detect the radio waves
sent by a working mobile phone. From now on until the end of
January, a total of 30 such devices will be tested on Lufthansa
flights, the company said.
</P>
<P>
The on-board use of mobile phone is banned because it can
disturb the electronic systems of an airliner. Under a law adopted
by the German government in summer, an offender could face up to
two years in jail in Germany. 
