<HEADLINE> Canada Provides 12,500 Tons of Relief Food to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- An aid agreement of
providing 12,500 tons of relief food to Ethiopia was signed here
today between the governments of Canada and Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is signed in response to the recent appeal to
the international community made by the Disaster Prevention and
Preparedness Commission of Ethiopia to mitigate food shortage
surfaced due to rain failure this year in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion, Disaster Prevention and Preparedness
