Canada had previously provided wheat valued at three million U.S.
Dollars through the World Food Program in response to the food
needs in pastoral areas.
</P>
<P>
Canada provides approximately 12,000 tons annually through
partner non-governmental organization for food for development
activities in food deficit areas throughout the country, the
ambassador added.
</P>
<P>
According to an earlier announcement from the Disaster
Prevention and Preparedness Commission of Ethiopia, over 4.2
million people need relief food of 572,835 tons in 1998. 
</P>
