<HEADLINE> Italy Supports Joint Cypriot Team for EU Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Italy wishes that the Turkish
Cypriots will join the delegation of Cyprus to negotiate the entry
of the island into the European Union (EU), a senior Italian
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Italy always supports the strategy of EU's enlargement and
Cypriot efforts to become an EU member, Italy's Deputy Foreign
Minister Piero Fassino told reporters after a meeting with
Cypriot Foreign Minister Ioannis Kasoulides of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Fassino said that the EU and Italy are convinced that "it is
important that this negotiation should be held by a Cypriot
delegation which could be represented by all components of the
island."
</P>
<P>
He said that during his separate meetings today with Cypriot
President Glafcos Clerides and Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf
Denktash, he made it clear that "Italy wishes there is a joint
delegation representing all the island."
</P>
<P>
Cyprus submitted its application in 1990 for full membership to
the EU, which has decided that the accession negotiations begin
early next year.
</P>
<P>
But the breakaway Turkish Cypriots opposed the move and
suspended its talks with the government on a peaceful solution to
their protracted problem.
</P>
<P>
The government has suggested that the Turkish Cypriots be
represented in the accession negotiations. The EU and its member
states have been intensifying efforts to persuade the Turkish
Cypriots to accept the proposal.
</P>
<P>
Fassino came here before a summit of the EU due next week in
Luxembourg to discuss the issue of enlargement, which is expected
to include Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into a Greek Cypriot south and a
Turkish Cypriot north since 1974 when Turkey sent troops to take
over the northern third following a failed pro-Athens coup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
