<HEADLINE> OIC Drafts Resolution on Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The meeting of experts of the
Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC) today approved a draft
resolution on the Afghan conflict, Iran's official news agency
IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
The draft resolution urged all Afghan groups to accept an
immediate and unconditional ceasefire and establish a broad-based
government.
</P>
<P>
It expressed support for all efforts made by all parties in
this regard, according to the agency.
</P>
<P>
The draft also called on all states to immediately end arms
supplies to the conflicting parties in Afghanistan, provide help
to Afghan refugees in Pakistan and Iran, and work for their speedy
and voluntary repatriation and rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
The meeting of experts of the OIC started on Tuesday in the
framework of political, economic and cultural committees.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman of the eighth OIC summit, Iranian
Deputy Foreign Minister Mohammad Java Zarif, the political
committee approved most of the draft resolutions today, leaving
the hot topics of Palestine and Iraq to the summit.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the economic committee has approved 37 draft
resolutions, such as the issue of how the Islamic world will be
prepared for the 21st century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
