<HEADLINE> Election Campaign Starts With Presidential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's nine Presidential
candidates today presented their papers to the new Chairman of
the Electorall Commission, Samuel Kivuitu, thus kicking off the
election campaigning for the December 29 General Election.
</P>
<P>
Kivuitu was appointed on Tuesday when former Chairman Z.R.
Chesoni was named Kenya's new Chief Justice.
</P>
<P>
Incumbent President Daniel arap Moi was the first presidential
candidate to present his papers and he was followed by opposition
Democratic Party of Kenya candidate Mwai Kibaki and later by
Raila Odinga of the National Democratic Party.
</P>
<P>
President Moi, 73, facing challenges from some new comers,
will be seeking the top seat, hoping to extend his 19 years
political career as president to 24 years.
</P>
<P>
Kibaki, 66, who was the presidential candidate in 1992
elections, will be returning to the coming presidential race
while Raila Odinga, Charity Ngilu and others are joining the race
as the new comers.
</P>
<P>
The presidential poll is believed to favour Moi and his ruling
Kenya African National Union because of division and poor
organization of the opposition parties.
</P>
<P>
Out of 27 registered political parties in the East African
country, 12 are expected to field presidential candidates for the
second multi-party elections.
</P>
<P>
Tomorrow is the deadline for the Presidential nomination.
</P>
