<HEADLINE> Macao Air Route Will Link Nanjing with Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- A chartered air service
agreement was signed here today for a new route from Nanjing, the
capital of China's Jiangsu province, to Taiwan via Macao.
</P>
<P>
The agreement between Air Macao, China Travel Service (Jiangsu)
Group Company, and Nanjing's Lukou Airport calls for flights to
begin December 29.
</P>
<P>
Air Macao said that it now has seven routes from the Chinese
mainland to Taiwan. According to today's agreement, there will be
two round-trip flights each week from next year.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu province now has more than 3,000 Taiwan-funded
enterprises, the largest number for any area on the mainland. The
new route is expected to improve economic and trade ties, tourist,
and cultural exchanges and co-operation between Jiangsu, in east
China, and Macao and Taiwan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
