<HEADLINE> Bangladesh PM on Peace Accord With Tribal Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina said that the peace agreement with Chittagong Hill Tracts
tribal leaders was "a milestone in our national development and
prosperity."
</P>
<P>
Addressing editors of the national newspapers and news agencies
in Dhaka this afternoon, the prime minister said, "We want peace
and stability and rational socio-economic development of all
regions of the country."
</P>
<P>
"We hope the agreement will put an end to the war-like
situation and fratricidal conflict which had long disturbed peace
and stability of the hilly regions," she stated.
</P>
<P>
She said that under the agreement full guarantee was given to
economic prosperity, social security and overall development for
the hilly region, and at the same time all legitimate rights and
privileges of the non-tribal citizens of the hilly districts were
protected under the terms of the agreement.
</P>
<P>
"All citizens of the country have equal rights" was the main
essence of the agreement signed between the government and the
tribal leaders, the prime minister stated.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the chronological development of the peace
initiatives, she acknowledged that "the governments before us had
also taken such steps and tried to bring peace in the region."
</P>
<P>
Efforts had been made for a long time to resolve the issue, she
said, adding the agreement was the "final outcome" of the long
initiatives to bring peace and stability in the hilly region.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after signing the agreement, heads of different
diplomatic missions and representatives of various donor agencies
in Dhaka expressed their earnest desire to help implement the
agreement, the prime minister told the editors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
