<HEADLINE> US Secretary of State to Visit Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Angolan Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Anercio Cadete confirmed here today that U. S.
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright will visit Angola on
December 12.
</P>
<P>
While revealing Albright's African tour, Cadete said, this is
Albright's first visit to Angola since she became the secretary
of state in January this year. She visited Angola last year when
she was U.S. representative to the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Albright's forthcoming visit to Angola aims to acquaint
herself with the preparations for the next meeting between heads
of Angola's warring sides, namely President Eduardo dos Santos
and Jonas Savimbi, chairman of the National Union for the Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
She will also want to get better understanding of the present
situation in the Angolan peace process and the problems it is
facing.
</P>
<P>
Observers here said as one of the three observing countries,
the United States plays a major role in the Angolan peace
process.
</P>
<P>
They believed that Albright's visit at this critical moment of
the implementation of the 1994 Lusaka Peace Accord, will surely
push forward the slowly moving peace process in the country.
</P>
<P>
This is Albright's first African tour after she took office as
secretary of state. Besides Angola, she will also visit Ethiopia,
Uganda, Rwanda, the Democratic Republic of Congo, South Africa
and Zimbabwe. 
</P>
