<HEADLINE> Tibet Gives Awards To Outstanding State-owned Enterprise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- China's Tibet Autonomous Region
gave an award of 250,000 yuan today to a leading State-owned beer
producer to promote reforms and to develop the economy here.
</P>
<P>
The award, which went to the Lhasa Beer Corporation Ltd., was
the first of its kind and bore the title "Leading Enterprise in
Reform". Also, the autonomous regional government decided to give
the company a refund as a reward. It has given 10.06 million yuan
in profits to the government.
</P>
<P>
However, the autonous regional government only kept 5 million
yuan and will return the remainder to the enterprises as its
development fund for next year.
</P>
<P>
The company had in fact run in the red for many years, and was
still 29-million yuan in debt just two years ago.
</P>
<P>
But, with 36-million yuan loaned from Sichuan Province, the
enterprise underwent a series of reforms and brought in advanced
technology and production equipment. It is now a key enterprise in
Tibet, with an annual production of 20,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Xu Mingyang, vice-chairman of the autonomous regional
government, called on the 700 State-owned enterprises in Tibet to
follow suit and carry out reforms to develop their production and
economy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
