<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New World Cultural Heritage Site in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- UNESCO today added Lijiang, an
ancient Chinese city in the southwestern province of Yunnan to its
list of World Cultural Heritage sites.
</P>
<P>
The 800-year-old city is the only one that is home to the Naxi
ethnic minority and is well-known for its house construction and
street layout. According to experts, an ethnic city that has been
preserved so well is unusual.
</P>
<P>
Lijiang was severely hit last year by an earthquake that
measured seven on the Richter Scale, but a group of visiting
UNESCO personnel this May said that the Chinese government had
done a good job of restoring it.
</P>
<P>
The World Cultural Heritage list has 500 sites worldwide, and
more than 10 of them are in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
