<HEADLINE> Porsche Sees Strong Start in New Business Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The German sportcar manufacturer
Porsche today reported a 16.3 percent rise in car sales for the
first four months of the current business year beginning August 1,
which brought its turnover to 1.28 billion marks (723 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The company sold 9,700 cars through November, with production
during the four-month period reaching 10,000 units.
</P>
<P>
Encouraged by the strong start, the company is anticipating the
sale of at least 38,000 units for the current business year ending
July 31, 1998, an increase of 18 percent over the 1996-97 level.
</P>
<P>
Porsche expects its turnover will amount to more than 4.5
billion marks (about 2.5 billion dollars), up 13 percent from the
previous business year. 
