<HEADLINE> China's Military Commission Asks Military To Improve Themselves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- China's Central Military
Commission recently referred a set of ways of implementing the
regulations on practicing economy and reducing expenditures to be
circulated throughout the People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
The regulations were formulated recently by the Party Central
Committee and State Council.
</P>
<P>
According to the ways for implementing the regulations that
have been subsequently worked out by the three PLA headquarters,
military offices at various levels can not build, expand, or
redecorate office buildings and various centers for the next three
years, and that costs for conferences, ceremonies, exchanges,
competitions, and news conferences should be strictly controlled,
and conferences held in scenic spots are to be sharply restricted.
</P>
<P>
When officers and enlisted personnel are on official
businesses, they can not spend large sums of public funds on
drinking, eating, and entertainment.
</P>
<P>
The methods of implementation also clearly defined that no one
can ask that a local telephone be installed unless he pays the
cost himself, and mobile phones need approval before they can be
purchased or used.
</P>
<P>
And it clearly outlines the use and replacement of cars and the
use of public funds for travel abroad.  
</P>
</TEXT>
