<HEADLINE> Southern China Development Zone Ready For Industrial Occupants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Yangpu Economic Development
Zone on China's island province of Hainan, after years of
infrastructure development, is finally ready for industrial
projects, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Yangpu is the first zone in China to be built by foreign
developers, who have spent four billion HK dollars on the
27.35-sq km. zone over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The completed work includes the first phase of a 315,500-kw
power plant, a 50-km road network, underground piping, the first
phase of Yangpu Port, and an expressway linking Yangpu with
Haikou, the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
A digital phone, mobile phone, and public data network have
also been built.
</P>
<P>
The developers have sold 770,000 sq.m. of space, about 7.6
percent of the available space.
</P>
<P>
Three industrial projects: a steel-rod plant, a rice-processing
mill, and a wood flooring factory have been set up in the zone.
</P>
