<HEADLINE> Senior Party Officials Asked to Study Deng Xiaoping Theory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee, today asked Party officials to study Deng Xiaoping
Theory and policies of the 15th Party national Congress more
extensively.
</P>
<P>
Hu made the remarks at the opening ceremony today of a course
on Deng Theory and the spirit of the 15th National Congress of the
CPC at the Party School of the Chinese Communist Party Central
Committee, of which he is president.
</P>
<P>
The course is for members and alternate members of the CPC
Central Committee. Hu asked them to play a leading role in holding
Deng's banner high and studying Deng Theory.
</P>
<P>
The decision to offer the course came in response to President
Jiang Zemin's report at the 15th Party Congress of the CPC and his
comment on improving senior officials' political awareness and
making them good theorists.
</P>
<P>
Hu asked officials to understand the theory by focusing on the
fundamental issue: "what is socialism and how to build socialism",
and said that they need to have an understanding of the theory's
historical significance and its guiding position. He said that
CPC members should bring the socialist cause pioneered Mao Zedong
and Deng Xiaoping and other revolutionaries into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Party officials should implement the 15th Party National
Congress policies emancipating their minds, seeking truth from
facts, seizing opportunities, and forging ahead, he said,
stressing the importance of combining theory with practice, which
is a Maxist working style. 
</P>
