<HEADLINE> EU Holds Meeting to Secure Oil, Gas Supplies to Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Oil-producing countries from
central Asia and from around the Caucasus and Black Sea areas met
today in a European Union conference on regional development of
oil and gas transmission infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the two-day meeting is both to help the newly
independent states (NIS) to modernize and extend the oil and gas
networks they inherited from the former Soviet Union and to ensure
trade and security of supply.
</P>
<P>
The conference launched a high-level debate among
representatives from the NIS states, the EU member states, eastern
and central Europe and Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The outcome of the meeting is expected to facilitate the flow
of oil and gas between the NIS states and to assist producers and
transit countries in accessing European markets.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, according to EU officials, is also important in
the context of the future enlargement of the 15-nation union in
that it will secure the necessary investment for the
interconnection of European networks with the oil and gas
transmission systems in the NIS states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
