<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 People Killed by Militiamen in S. Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Military sources in
southeastern Sierra Leone charged today that an upsurge in
attacks by the Kamajor militiamen has killed three people,
including a business woman recently.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, traditional hunters known as
Kamajors ambushed a commercial truck with over 200 bags of rice
on Wednesday in Jembeh along the Bo-Kenema road in the eastern
part of the country.
</P>
<P>
"They shot and killed Musu Kannch, a business woman who owned
part of the rice stock as well as two men who wanted to put up
resistance," an eye witness said, adding that another man was
seriously wounded in the attack.
</P>
<P>
Kamajors also attacked a Sierra Leone Red Cross truck in
Moyamba in the south, stripped naked a west European official
belonging to the organization and forced three Sierra Leone
officials to lie down for several hours in the sun before they
were released and the relief consignment seized.
</P>
<P>
Unconfirmed reports said the Red Cross has suspended its
operations in the area as a result of the attack. 
</P>
</TEXT>
