<HEADLINE> Police Seize 27.5 Kilograms of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Guangdong and Guizhou
police have smashed a drug trafficking gang and seized 27.5
kilograms of heroin.
</P>
<P>
Six suspects involved in the drug case were arrested with
400,000 yuan and a motorcycle used in drug trafficking and
smuggling was seized.
</P>
<P>
In October, the Guizhou Provincial Public Security Department
was informed that the gang was going to transfer heroin from
southwestern China's Yunnan Province to Guangzhou, capital of
southern China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Acting on the tip, Guangzhou police immediately organized a
task force for 24-day surveillance which led to the arrest of five
suspects.
</P>
<P>
Guizhou Province police and their colleagues from Guangzhou
went to Puning City in Guizhou and arrested Chen Songyou for drug
trafficking and seized 27.5 kilograms of heroin, 400,000 yuan and
the motorcycle.
</P>
<P>
Police also believe that Chen has sold 3.8-kilograms heroin in
Puning City since 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
