<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five Chinese Scientists Win Prestigious Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Five Chinese scientists and
technicians were honored for achievements in their fields
with a Wong Tanping Science Award here today, each receiving
100,000 yuan (12,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Wong Tanping Science Award was established in 1992 by Wong
Tanping, a well-known Hong Kong entrepreneur who contributed 5
million U.S. dollars to establish the prize.
</P>
<P>
The annual award is given to five outstanding scientists and
engineers chosen from among the winners of the scientists
and engineers in scientific and technological development.
</P>
<P>
The '97 Wong Tanping Science Award winners are: Li Zaiting,
senior engineer of the petrochemicals Engineering Research
Institute; Rong Tingzhao, a professor at Sichuan Agricultural
University; Xu Duanyi, a professor at Qinghua University; Cheng
Zhaogu, a researcher for Shanghai Institute of Optics and Fine
Mechanics under the Chinese Academy of Sciences; and Xin Zhiyong,
director of the Institute of Crop Breeding and Cultivation under
the Chinese Academy of Agricultural Sciences.
</P>
<P>
Li Zaiting's technique of catalytic cracking process in
petrochemical production has met the world's most advanced
standards.
</P>
<P>
Rong Tingzhao has made outstanding research achievements in
cross-breeding corn.
</P>
<P>
Xu Duanyi has developed a series of optical techniques, many of
which have been adopted by more than 40 foreign companies.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Zhaogu is a leader in the development of laser equipment.
</P>
<P>
Xin Zhiyong has bred new strains of wheat, which are
disease-resistant.  
</P>
</TEXT>
