<DOCNO> XIE19971204.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Needs to Improve Management of Materials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania need to improve
poor management of materials have caused huge losses to the
country, Vice-President Dr Omar Ali Juma said.
</P>
<P>
"It is sad to note that the meagre resources that we possess
have often been wasted, lost either deliberately or due to lack
of necessary knowledge," Juma told the 12th Materials Management
Professionals' Annual Conference, held in the northern region of
Arusha Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Vice-president attributed the losses to the failure of
using professionals appropriately, saying the materials
management sector actually has enough manpower to control the
situation.
</P>
<P>
Competent professionals must be utilized to ensure that all
kinds of materials are properly managed, Juma told 160 delegates
to the conference.
</P>
<P>
In order to save the nation from huge losses, those who manage
the materials and purchase goods must have relevant skills,
knowledge and necessary qualifications to undertake the job, Juma
said in a speech read on his behalf by the Arusha Regional
Commissioner, Daniel Ole Njolay.
</P>
<P>
"I emphasize that those who are not professionally trained
should not be let to perform the materials management functions,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
On environment, which is the main theme of this year's
conference, the Vice-president urged the materials management
officials to procure environment friendly materials and avoid
hazards in transportation, distribution and storage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
