<DOCNO> XIE19971204.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia Urged to Strengthen Regional Transport Links </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Asian-Pacific transport and
communications officials and experts here today urged the
governments in the region to speed up the region's infrastructure
development, especially those regional transport projects.
</P>
<P>
The call was made during the Third Session of the Transport and
Communications Committee of the United Nations Economic and Social
Commission for Asia and the Pacific (ESCAP), which closed here
today.
</P>
<P>
Efficient and reliable transport and communications systems are
indispensable for national economic and social development and for
countries' integration into the regional and the global economy,
said the delegates from 28 Asian-Pacific countries.
</P>
<P>
They also stressed the importance of the Regional Action
Program (RAP) adopted at the Ministerial Conference on
Infrastructure in New Delhi in October 1996.
</P>
<P>
The program contained 64 activities, such as the Asian Land
Transport Infrastructure Development (ALTID) project encompassing
the Trans-Asia Railway (TAR) and the Asian Highway.
</P>
<P>
It was introduced with an aim to implement the New Delhi Action
Plan on Infrastructure Development in Asia and the Pacific, which
was adopted at the 51st Session of the ESCAP Commission in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The four-day event was also briefed on the development of
Asia-Europe land bridges, including the UN projects on Transport
Corridor Europe Caucasus Asia (TRACECA), a "new silk road", and
north-south corridors, namely, Northern Europe-Russia-Central
Asia-Persian Gulf Corridor and North-East Asia Corridor.
</P>
<P>
On other areas, participants attending the meeting showed great
concern over the cross-border transport of dangerous goods, urging
Asian-Pacific countries to toughen their rules and regulations and
set up related bodies to curb the problem.
</P>
<P>
They also proposed to establish an interim secretariat of the
Asia Infrastructure Development Alliance within ESCAP to promote
the private sector's participation in the regional infrastructure
development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
