<DOCNO> XIE19971204.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Secures Chinese Soccer League Title in Advance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, CHINA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Dalian
Wanda succeeded in retaining the title of the Chinese Soccer
League in advance after beating Guangzhou Apollo 2-0 on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Wanda secured the title with five rounds remained and improved
its unbeaten record to 51, the third that Wanda pockets the title
in the four-year-old league wherein the squad also won in 1994 and
1996.
</P>
<P>
Wanda's head coach Chi Shangbin said that "I hope the China
soccer move into the top class in Asia with great potentials to
compete against the best teams in the world."
</P>
<P>
From 14 wins and three draws, Wanda has scored 45 points after
the 17th round, 16 points clear of second placer Shanghai Shenhua
and third-ranked Beijing Guo'an, who would still lagged behind one
point even with a 100 percent record in the remaining matches.
</P>
<P>
Wanda, who has won the title first time at home, took the most
possession of the match by scoring the first in the 28th minute
when Wang Tao curled an angled free-kick on the brink of the box.
</P>
<P>
Four minutes before the break, Wang Tao's flank cross flew
towards Hao Haidong, top scorer with 11 in the league, who chested
down the ball before an Apollo defender tapped in an own goal.
</P>
<P>
Wanda kept its momentum in the up front but failed to extend
the lead with poor finishes in the second half.
</P>
<P>
The home spectators were filled with joys and flamed fireworks
to celebrate the club's victory after the game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
