(Brunei) via Kota Kinabalu (Malaysia) will be operated exclusively
with A320, benefiting passengers on this sector with business
class service for the first time.
</P>
<P>
For years, PAL served this route with the older,
all-economy-class Boeing 737s.
</P>
<P>
PAL said that it is also mounting more seat offerings on its
services to Singapore, Jakarta, Ho Chi Minh City and Bandar Seri
Begawan Via Kota Kinabalu during the months of December 1997 and
January 1998.
</P>
<P>
PAL is in the process of phasing in new aircraft to its
regional routes as it continues to improve passenger services in
this important area of operations. For the key Southeast Asian
market, the airline's workhorses are the widebody Airbus A330 and
the single-aisle A320.  
</P>
