<HEADLINE> Huangshan Scenery Attracts More Overseas Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 4 (Xinhua) -- A record 190,000 overseas
tourists visited Huangshan in east China's Anhui Province during
the first 10 months of this year to enjoy the well-known natural
scenery on Huangshan Mountain.
</P>
<P>
The number of overseas tourists visiting the area during the
first ten months of 1997 more than doubled the number for the 1996
period. Huangshan led the nation's top 24 cities with famous
scenic attractions in the number of foreign visitors.
</P>
<P>
More than 3.7 million overseas and domestic tourists visited
Huangshan during the first 10 months of the year, up 36 percent on
the 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations has listed Huangshan Mountain scenic sites
as protected natural and cultural areas.
</P>
<P>
The city's extensive efforts to improve the construction of
infrastructure has also contributed a great deal to the rising of
the number of tourists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
