<HEADLINE> Shanghai Shipping Exchange Plays Major Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The year-old Shanghai Shipping
Exchange has played a major role in standardizing market
activities, exchanging information and regulating prices.
</P>
<P>
The exchange completed 364 million in transactions for 36
million tons of goods and 30 vessels by the end of October this
year. The exchange also handled auctions for ships valued at
nearly five million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Members of the exchange have access to customs clearance
services, with over 80 percent of local shipping agents located
near its headquarters on Dongdaming Road.
</P>
<P>
The exchange issues timely information on the shipping
industry, and is extending great effort to curb market disorders
in order to stabilize prices and promote market development.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, the exchange has 184 members, compared with 116 in
the very beginning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
