<HEADLINE> Restrictions to Be Imposed on Heavy Trucks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Uganda is to restrict heavily
loaded vehicles from entering the country, a senior government
official has said.
</P>
<P>
Wanjusi Sasieba, the State Minister for Works, Transort and
Commnication, said on Monday that his government has imformed its
neighboring countries that vehicles entering his country must
observe a restriction about specific tonnage for the concerned
vehicles, otherwise, drivers will be fined.
</P>
<P>
According to Kampala traffic boss Grace Turyagumanawe,the
existing traffic laws in the country are " outdated and difficult
to enforce", though the traffic condition in the countrya has been
improved due to the efforts made by local governments and police.
</P>
<P>
The parliament will soon amend the traffic law published in
1970, Wasieba said at the opening ceremony of Uganda Road
Accident Reduction Network Organisation. 
