<HEADLINE> Hainan Develops Overseas Fishing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Two fishing vessels from south
China's Hainan Province are sailing to waters in southwestern
Pacific.
</P>
<P>
The Hainan Ocean Fisheries Corp., owner of the vessels, is the
island's first enterprise to participate in the highly competitive
international fisheries industry, as well as the first to extend
efforts to improve its overseas market.
</P>
<P>
The vessels are bound for fishing grounds some 3,000 nautical
miles from Hainan. The area is well-known for its abundant aquatic
resources.
</P>
<P>
The corporation invested over three million yuan (375,000
U.S. dollars) to fabricate and equip the vessels which will sell
this year's catch on the international market. 
</P>
