<HEADLINE> Province Seeks to Increase Scientific Cooperation With Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Heilongjiang Province in
northeast China is seeking further cooperation with 36 Russian
science and research institutes.
</P>
<P>
During the last six years, the province and Russian institutes
have collaborated on 48 projects, 16 of which have been listed by
China's State Science and Technology Commission as International
Science and Technology Cooperative Projects, said an official of
Heilongjiang's Science and Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
Bordering Russia and known as northern China's granary, the
province has special interest in Russia's agricultural
techniques. The province's Academy of Agricultural Sciences
initiated cooperation with its Russian counterpart.
</P>
<P>
Techniques of seed coating and crop-growth adjusting provided
by the Russians have helped the province increase its grain output
by 10 percent and vegetable output by more than 30 percent in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The imported sea buckthorn's productivity was 10 times local
varieties, and its resistance to wind and drought proved valuable
in the saline-alkali soil in the province's western portion.
</P>
<P>
An important center of China's heavy industry, the province has
more than 600 large and medium-size state enterprises, some of
which were built with the help of the former Soviet Union.
</P>
</TEXT>
