<HEADLINE> Ningbo Airport to Expand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Republic of Korea has signed
a contract to provide a loan of five million US dollars to fund an
expansion project at the Ningbo Airport in east China's Zhejiang
Province.
</P>
<P>
The Export-Import Bank of Korea will provide the funds for the
second phase construction at the Lishe Airport, with related
projects including the construction of boarding facilities and the
installation of electronic screens in the passenger terminal to
list flight schedules.
</P>
<P>
The airport served well over one million passengers in 1996,
almost double its designed annual handling capacity of 510,000
passengers.
</P>
<P>
Second phase construction will be carried out at an estimated
cost of 880 million yuan, with some 400 million yuan earmarked for
improving the passenger terminal.
</P>
<P>
The project will increase the airport's annual handling
capacity to 3.8 million passengers and 46,700 tons of
cargo. 
