<HEADLINE> East China City Restructures Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIANYUNGANG, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Ruyi Company, a local
enterprise producing processed agricultural goods, has associated
itself with 24 enterprises through shareholding, loans and mergers.
</P>
<P>
Seeking capital expansion as Ruyi did is an important approach
in industrial restructuring in this east China port city.
</P>
<P>
The city's Hengrui Group, which was newly created after the
merger of the Hengrui Company and Zhongjin Company, for instance,
has combined advantages in technology, production and land
use. The sales revenue of the group in the first eight months was
nearly 200 million yuan.
</P>
