HANOI -- Deputies at Vietnam's National Assembly have
reportedly claimed that the gap is widening between the country's
rich and poor due to inadequate government policies.
</P>
<P>
Deputies told the on-going assembly session that the disparity
was growing in the countryside itself and between rural and urban
areas, the latest issue of Vietnamese Investment Review reported.
(Vietnam-National Assembly) 
