<HEADLINE> China and Japan Cooperate on Dental Technician Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-Japan Dental
Technician Training Center, established to teach lab workers how
to make false teeth, is open now in Chengdu, capital of southwest
China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The center aims to conduct a dental technician training program
and courses as well as establishing a system and curriculum for
the certified academic qualifications for dental technicians in
Sichuan and all other provinces.
</P>
<P>
In Japan, manufacturing false teeth has become an
industry. Japan has 35,000 dental technicians and one dentist with
a college education background for every 3,000 people, according
to Wu Dayi, director of the Dental Implantology Center (DIC) of
the Huaxi University of Medical Sciences.
</P>
<P>
China has about 100,000 dentists, a small number when compared
to its large population. Eighty percent of false teeth and dental
materials have to be imported, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
The center was jointly set up by DIC of the university and
Japanese Shofu Inc. as well as the Shin-Osaka Dental Technician
College, famous for dental education and dental material
manufacturing in Japan.
</P>
<P>
A "Cooperation Agreement for the Conduct of Dental
Technological Education" was also signed at the center's opening
ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
