<HEADLINE> Machinery Industry Improves in Zhejiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 4 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
has decided to support 25 major large machinery company groups by
introducing high-technology and restructuring assets in the next
three years.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that increasing technical competence of the
province's machinery industry and making full use of funds are
important steps.
</P>
<P>
So far, the province has invested 2 billion yuan (250 million
U.S. dollars) in more than 100 projects involving technological
innovation in the industry.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 machinery groups have been established, with the
total registered capital and sales volume accounting for one-third
of the province's total in this sector, which has been playing an
increasingly important role in the province's economy.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province's machinery industry accounted for more
than 20 billion yuan (2.5 billion U.S. dollars) in sales and 2
billion yuan (250 million U.S. dollars) in profits and taxes, with
exports reaching 427 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The province will pay particular attention to facilities for
transport and telecommunications and complete sets of mechanical
equipment, mainly including 50 kinds of products such as
motorcycles, automobiles, steam turbines and numerically
controlled machine tools.
</P>
<P>
To date, industrial output from high-tech mechanical products
consists of 50 percent of the industry's total in the province.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 2000, 10 of these 25 company groups will sell
more than 1 billion yuan (125 million U.S. dollars) and have 100
million yuan (12.5 million U.S. dollars) of profits and taxes.
</P>
</TEXT>
