<HEADLINE> Investment Soars in Philippine Economic Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Investments registered with the
Philippine Economic Zone Authority (PEZA) soared to a record-high
of 4.4 billion U.S. dollars in the first 11 months this year,
local television reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Citing data issued by the PEZA Wednesday, the reports said the
latest investment figure more than doubled the 1.9 billion dollars
investments in the economic zones in all of last year.
</P>
<P>
The PEZA, which manages 65 economic zones all over the country,
said substantial investments flew in during the third quarter even
at the height of the region's financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
During the third quarter this year, the economic zones drew a
total of 2.3 billion dollars foreign and domestic investments.
</P>
<P>
PEZA Director-General Lilia de Lima was quoted as saying the
investment figure for the third quarter was "really amazing" since
everybody thought investments would slow down due to Asia's
financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
De Lima predicted more investments in the economic zones this
year as many foreign firms are awaiting approval of their projects
from the government.  
</P>
