<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Montedison Establishes Three More Joint Ventures in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Montedison has established
three more joint venture projects in China, making it the major
Italian investor in the nation with total investments topping 300
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Montedison CEO Enrco Bondi said the three new joint ventures
include a pharmaceutical joint venture with Shanghai Xianfeng
(Pioneer) Pharmaceutical Co. which was established at a cost of 30
million U.S. dollars, a fire extinguisher manufacturing plant
established with the Zhejiang Juhua Group Co., and a specialized
feed processing plant in Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Bondi expressed an extraordinary interest in the Chinese
market, and noted that Montedison, the second largest private
enterprise in Italy, is proud of having over 40 years of
cooperative ties with China.
</P>
<P>
Montedison's two previous direct investments include a joint
venture pharmaceutical plant established with the Qilu
Pharmaceutical Company. The plant is scheduled to begin operations
before the end of December.
</P>
<P>
Eridania Benghin-Say, a Montedison subsidiary, will operate the
parent company's largest project in China, a joint venture corn
flour processing plant established with the Jifa Co. in northeast
China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, which will feature state-of-the-art
technology and will be the most advanced plant of its kind in
Asia, is scheduled to enter operations in 1999. The plant, the
largest of its kind in China, will have an annual processing
capacity of 300,000 tons of corn.
</P>
<P>
Montedison has invested in China's agriculture, processing,
pharmaceutical and chemical industries. The company and its
subsidiaries have also been active in minerals exploration over
the past decade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
