<HEADLINE> Finance Experts Call for Market Modernization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-four finance ministers
from 34 American countries today called for strengthening and
modernizing the region's financial markets.
</P>
<P>
The ministers made the appeal in a joint statement at the end
of the Second Meeting of Finance Ministers of the Americas.
</P>
<P>
The participants pointed out the needs for preparation for the
effective management of international crises that may occur in the
future, despite achievements the region has made in establishing
suitable and coherent macro-economic policies.
</P>
<P>
They also underlined the necessity of tightening governmental
regulations and surveillance over the activities of the region's
banks and stock exchanges, and reiterated their commitments to
furthering hemispheric integration.
</P>
<P>
At the two-day forum, the ministers discussed recent financial
crises in Asia, macro economic stability as well as modernization
and integration of financial markets.
</P>
<P>
Conclusions drawn at the forum are expected to be analyzed at
the next summit of the Americas to be held here in April 1998.
</P>
