<HEADLINE> RBI Plans Direct Participation in Refinancing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Reserve Bank of India
(RBI) plans to get directly involved in refinancing the
infrastructure sector in the wake of a tardy flow of bank credit
to the sector, a government official said here today.
</P>
<P>
RBI Governor Bimal Jalan has already discussed the issue with
Finance Minister P. Chidambaram and he has also initiated a
dialogue within the RBI to work out a mechanism to enhance the
comfort levels of involvement by banks and financial institutions
(FIs) in funding commercially viable projects in the power,
telecom, road and ports sectors.
</P>
<P>
One of the problems faced by banks and FIs is the long
repayment period, often extending to 12-15 years, for loans to
infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
Despite its best efforts, the government has not succeeded in
persuading banks and FIs to increase their credit flow because of
the risks they may face in the infrastructure sector.
</P>
<P>
The RBI's involvement will help change their perception, the
official said.  
</P>
