<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal, Oman Sign Air Services Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Nepal and Oman have signed a
memorandum of understanding on air services, Nepal's official RSS
news agency said Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Under the document signed recently in Mascot, capital of Oman,
designated airlines of the two countries will operate seven
passenger and seven cargo flights every week between the Nepali
capital of Kathmandu and Mascot.
</P>
<P>
The airlines are also entitled to operate multiple designation
flights under the document, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
So far Nepal has signed bilateral air services agreements with
27 countries including Oman.  
</P>
</TEXT>
