<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albanian Refugees in Italy Forced to Return Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 3 (Xinhua) -- An Italian military plane today
carried more than 80 Albanians out of Italy.
</P>
<P>
The deportees, among the 16,000 Albanians arrived in southern
Italy earlier this year, were the first group of refugees forced
to leave.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Italian authorities have a plan to send back
more Albanian nationals -- most of them reluctant to leave Italy
and some have gone on hunger strike -- by ship on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Previously, the government ordered in August to return some
5,000 illegal immigrants by November 30.
</P>
<P>
The Albanians fled to Italy in spring in the wake of violent
protests and armed riots in their their tiny Balkan country
following the collapse of high-risk pyramid investment schemes.
</P>
</TEXT>
