<DOCNO> XIE19971204.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing Enterprises Subscribe to ISO9000 Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- An increasing number of local
enterprises in southwest China's Chongqing Municipality are
working hard to attain the ISO9000 certification to become more
competitive on the international market.
</P>
<P>
So far, nine large enterprises have received ISO9000 quality
certification, said sources from the Chongqing Import and Export
Commodity Inspection Bureau. According to the sources, another
nine enterprises will gain the certification by the end of this
year.
</P>
<P>
The bureau realized early the importance of carrying out
ISO9000 quality standards, and Chongqing is one of the pioneers in
promoting ISO9000 in southwest China, said Zhong Dechang, director
of the bureau.
</P>
<P>
Since the Southwest China Aluminum Processing Plant in 1993
became the first large enterprise in the country to receive the
ISO9000 certification, its products are traded on the London
market for nonferrous metals.
</P>
<P>
China Jialing Industrial Co., Ltd. (Group), the largest
state-grade enterprise group in the motorcycle trade in China, can
manufacture two million motorcycles each year and 97 percent of
motorcycles are up to standard, an increase of four percentage
points since it received the certification.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the group has established overseas agencies and
the motorcycles are exported to more than 40 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Zhong said the practice of ISO9000 has helped many local
enterprises upgrade product quality, raise their prestige, and
enter the international market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
