<HEADLINE> Democratics Seek City Bids for 2000 Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic National
Committee (DNC) Wednesday invited 27 cities to compete for hosting
its national convention in 2000.
</P>
<P>
The cities invited include many that have hosted past national
political conventions. Most were chosen because their mayors had
informally expressed interest to President Bill Clinton, officials
said.
</P>
