<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The U.N. Security Council Wednesday again
urged Iraq to cooperate fully with UNSCOM, the U.N. Special
Commission in charge of dismantling Iraq's weapons of mass
destruction.
</P>
<P>
The Council made the appeal in its presidential statement
endorsing the recommendations of the latest UNSCOM report for full
and expeditious implementation of the relevant U.N. resolutions on
UNSCOM work. (UN-Iraq)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. Federal Reserve said today that American
manufacturers and farmers are starting to feel the impact of
financial crisis in some Asian nations.
</P>
<P>
"Asian financial turmoil and currency weakness have adversely
affected demand for manufactured and agricultural exports," the
Fed said in its "Beige Book" report, a survey of economic
conditions by its 12 district banks. (Fed-Report-Asia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BONN -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu will face a
tough test when he comes to Bonn to meet German Chancellor Helmut
Kohl on Thursday evening, German press reports quoted diplomatic
sources as saying Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu had to convince Kohl that he was planning to take
concrete steps towards peace, otherwise he would risk an attitude
change in Germany's Middle East policy, the German news agency DPA
quoted western diplomats as saying. (Germany-Israel-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- An Italian court in Milan sentenced former Prime
Minister Silvio Berlusconi on Wednesday to 16 months in jail for
false accounting.
</P>
<P>
A judge said the billionaire opposition leader, media magnet
had been found guilty but would not go to jail. He was released
after the court ordered an immediate remission of the same term.
(Italy-Trial)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The British government announced here Wednesday that
Britain would undertake its first ever naval exercises with Russia
in an effort to pave the way for future joint humanitarian actions.
</P>
<P>
British Defense Secretary George Robertson was quoted by the
Reuters as saying Wednesday, "Building mutual trust and confidence
through defense diplomacy is a vital element in European
security."  (UK-Russia-Naval Exercises)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The Irish government has welcomed Britain's action to
repatriate three Irish Republican Army (IRA) prisoners to Ireland.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Wednesday the three IRA guerillas have been flown by a
British helicopter to a jail in the Irish town of Portlaoise,
according to press reports from Dublin.
(Ireland-UK-Prisoners-Repatriation) 
</P>
