<HEADLINE> New Expressway in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Construction of an expressway
between Jieshou, a border city in Central China's Henan Province,
and Bengbu in neighboring Anhui Province, commenced recently.
</P>
<P>
The expressway will run 209.7 km through most of northern
Anhui, including the Yanhuai Plains, one of China's largest
agricultural zones, and will join another expressway running to
Hefei, the capital of Anhui, and Xuzhou in Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The project will be completed at an estimated cost of 3.34
billion yuan, with first phase construction scheduled for
completion in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
A local government official said the expressway is vitally
important for accelerating economic growth in northern
Anhui. 
