<HEADLINE> Nicaraguan Government, Armed Group Sign Peace Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Nicaraguan government today
signed the final version of a peace agreement with the country's
last armed guerrilla group.
</P>
<P>
The accord, the result of talks in the past two months, was
signed by President Arnoldo Aleman and Chief of the United Andres
Castro Front (UACF) Edmundo Garcia Olivas.
</P>
<P>
Only with stability and peace, Aleman said, the country has the
possibilities to develop the economy, alleviate the poverty and
improve living conditions for the people.
</P>
<P>
Olivas said his group will continue struggling with different
methods since there are still revolts in Nicaragua.
</P>
<P>
"Our goal is to integrate not only our armed men to the
community, but also peasants and their families. We must not
forget that in all wars, the most affected sectors are always the
poor," he said.
</P>
<P>
Under the peace accord, the first UACF group will hand in their
weapons today while the second one on December 12. The final group
is scheduled to be disarmed on December 19.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, the Nicaraguan government signed peace
agreements with the North Front 3-80 and the United Revolutionary
Front, the two groups with some 1,445 armed men. 
</P>
</TEXT>
