<HEADLINE> Chinese Researchers Looking For Way to Prevent Stomach Cancer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese researchers are
studying areas that report high rates of stomach cancer in hopes
of finding ways to prevent and treat the disease.
</P>
<P>
A special project is underway in Liaoning province in the
northeast China, where 30 people were found to have stomach cancer
during a random study of 2,901 people in the area.
</P>
<P>
Data is being collected in the tumor-prone area, and doctors
hope to develop effective ways to deal with the disease through
early diagnosis and treatment, as well as prevention, to reduce
the incidence.
</P>
<P>
The 30 patients are being treated at the Tumor Research
Institute of China Medical University. Doctors are also providing
medicine for local people in what they call an intervention
program.
</P>
<P>
Medical experts say that stomach cancer causes more deaths
than any other cancers in China. 
