mountain peak measuring 8,011 meters above sea level in Kashi
Prefecture of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The discovery brings the world's number of mountains exceeding
8,000 meters to 15.
</P>
<P>
Named "Central Peak," this mountain is on the main ridge of the
Karakorum Mountains and 8.35 kilometers to the southeast of Mount
Qogir, the world's second highest, and ranks 15th in terms of
height.
</P>
<P>
The mountain was found by Chinese geologists when making a map
of the Mount Qogir.  
