<HEADLINE> Private Economy in Chongqing Plays Important Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The private economy in
Chongqing, a newly established municipality in southwest China,
has maintained an annual growth rate of more than 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Local statistics show that in 1996 the total number of private
enterprises had reached more than 13,600, with a combined
industrial output of 6.66 billion yuan (830 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Last year, the city's private enterprises turned over 680
million yuan (85 million U.S. dollars) in taxes, accounting for 10
percent of the city's revenue.
</P>
<P>
Private enterprises have shifted from catering, trade and
service industries to manufacturing parts for automobiles and
motorcycles, real estate and tourism.
</P>
<P>
Some 320 private enterprises have been engaged in the
electronics industry, biological projects and the production of
pollution-free food (a kind of high-quality, nutritious food
produced strictly under national hygiene standards).
</P>
<P>
Altogether, 1,294 private enterprises own more than 1 million
yuan in registered capital each, and 63 of them have more than 10
million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
These private enterprises have absorbed more than 3,000 skilled
personnel including 600 professors, doctors and senior engineers,
according to the statistics. 
</P>
