<HEADLINE> Itlay's Former Premier Sentenced to 16 Months in Jail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 3 (Xinhua) -- An Italian court in Milan
sentenced former Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi on Wednesday to
16 months in jail for false accounting.
</P>
<P>
A judge said the billionaire opposition leader, media magnet
had been found guilty but would not go to jail. He was released
after the court ordered an immediate remission of the same term.
</P>
<P>
Berlusconi, who served as prime minister for seven months in
1994, was accused of false accounting in a case involving the
acquisition of a film business by his business group Fininvest.
</P>
<P>
The court also fined Berlusconi 60 million lire (35,000
U.S. dollars) but this was later reduced to 10 million lire (6,000
dollars). 
