<HEADLINE> Shanghai Taxi Runs on Liquefied Gas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The first taxi fueled by
liquefied natural gas recently appeared on Shanghai's streets
after the city completed its first liquefied gas station.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai expects its 40,000 taxis and public buses to be fueled
by liquefied gas within five years, said local officials.
</P>
<P>
The city has made efforts to purify exhaust gases to protect
the atmosphere in recent years. The use of liquefied gas in cars
is one method to improve the city's air quality.
</P>
<P>
Since Dec. 1, drivers are required to fix exhaust gas
purification devices to their cars and encouraged to use lead-free
petroleum. 
</P>
