<HEADLINE> FIA Gets IOC's Provisional Recognition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The International Automobile
Federation (FIA) was granted on Wednesday provisional recognition
by the International Olympic Committee (IOC) executive board.
</P>
<P>
The Paris-based world motor governing body became the latest
federation to win IOC's recognition which can become permanent
after two years.
</P>
<P>
IOC director general Francois Carrard meanwhile stressed that
FIA is not trying to become an Olympic sport.
</P>
<P>
"This has nothing to do with placing auto racing on the Olympic
program, it is clear they are not seek can be interesting for us,
and they recognize the overall role the IOC is leading," said
Carrard.
</P>
<P>
The IOC now recognizes 25 non-Olympic sports, including
ballroom dancing, surfing and rugby, according to sports director
Gilbert Felli. 
