<HEADLINE> Ningde to Host First China Yellow Croaker Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, December 4 (Xinhua) -- China's first yellow croaker
festival will be inaugurated on Dec. 18 in Ningde, a city in east
China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The yellow croaker is one of the four major kinds of fish in
China, with the annual catching volume topping 120,000 tons. The
Guanjingyang aquatic center in Ningde is one of China's largest
breeding centers for yellow croakers.
</P>
<P>
During the five-day festival, representatives from domestic and
overseas fisheries will attend an aquatic products exposition to
demonstrate their specialities. In addition, more than 200
projects will be open for investment.
</P>
<P>
Ningde has 48 enterprises engaged in yellow croaker breeding,
with a combined output reaching 51 million fish. This year, the
city bred 700 tons of yellow croaker valued at 160 million yuan
(19 million U.S. dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
