<HEADLINE> UK Shares' Rally Runs out of Steam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The previous two days'
rally on Europe's Leading stock markets ran out of steam
Wednesday and major index ended mixed, with London and Paris
all finishing slightly down while Frankfurt with moderate
gains.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE 100 index ended 6.9 points lower at
4,970.7 in thin trading as Britain's monetary policy
committee today started a two-day meeting on base interest
rates.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a weak performance in New York today and Asian
markets' recent turbulence all hit market sentiment, with
volumes remaining low in both the cash and futures market.
</P>
<P>
"It's very quiet and there's very little business about,"
said one dealer.
</P>
<P>
On the Paris bourse, the CAC-40 index also finished in
the negative ground, down 10.74 points at 2,902.35, just
above the 2,900-point level.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that stocks drifted lower as the dollar
retreated against the franc.
</P>
<P>
However, German shares ended slightly firmer, with the
DAX-30 index 9.93 points higher at 4,082.89 after a see-saw
session.
</P>
<P>
Traders said that the market was quiet due to the absence
of any motivating factors both at home and abroad. 
</P>
